caseTitle: Muhammad Raza Hayat Hiraj v. The Election Commission of Pakistan, Islamabad & others
tagline: The interlocutory orders passed by the Election Tribunal were not liable to be set aside by the High Court in its constitutional jurisdiction as the petitioners before the High Court had a remedy available to them by way of appeal under section 67 of the Representation of the People Act, 1976 after disposal of the election petitions.
